==English==
===Etymology===
The German interjection [[ach]] + [[Laut]] (‘sound’).

===Noun===
'''ach-laut''' (''plural:'' '''ach-lauts''')

# The gutteral [[kh]] phoneme (x) of German [[ach]], [[Achtung]], as opposed to the much softer [[ich-laut]] (χ) of the word [[ich]]. The ach-laut is also found in numerous other languages, including Hebrew, Dutch, Russian, and Scottish ([[loch]]). It is produced with high subglottal pressure in which the back of the tongue interacts with the soft palate. In German, it is employed after the written vowels a, o, u or the diphthong au.

====Translations====
*German: [[Ach-Laut]] {{m}}

